\begin_layout Standard
To Hilderich, it was unfathomable how any man could navigate practically
 blindly, without a map or a solid point of reference, simply by hunch and
 a general feeling of direction, both even more easily fooled in a chaotic
 mass of vegetation such as the one they were entangled in currently.
